Yeah, I suspect so.

07:50.080 --> 07:52.480
You go to work at Citibank.

07:52.480 --> 07:54.320
You walk in first day.

07:54.320 --> 07:54.880
What's that like?

07:56.560 --> 07:57.680
Trading floor is a big place.

07:58.960 --> 08:02.560
I remember getting the train to Canary Wharf

08:02.560 --> 08:05.600
and the Jubilee line makes this sort of like whooping sound.

08:05.600 --> 08:07.760
It's not like the trains that go past my window.

08:09.600 --> 08:11.120
Yeah, I remember they walked me in.

08:11.120 --> 08:13.520
I remember just seeing like massive, massive floor.

08:13.520 --> 08:16.480
I think the big thing that hits you about the trading floor is all these screens.

08:16.480 --> 08:19.440
It's like every trader has like a wall of like nine screens.

08:19.440 --> 08:20.960
Massive wall of screens like that.

08:20.960 --> 08:24.320
And they walk me around and they sort of sat me down,

08:25.600 --> 08:29.040
introduced me to the boss of the desk.

08:29.040 --> 08:32.080
And the boss is high and then he just ignores you, right?

08:32.080 --> 08:33.520
And you're sort of, you're sitting there.

08:33.520 --> 08:34.400
Nobody says anything to you.

08:34.400 --> 08:36.080
This is a thing that have very common experience

08:36.080 --> 08:37.760
when you start on trading floors is everyone says hi

08:37.760 --> 08:39.040
and then they just totally ignore you.

08:39.040 --> 08:43.120
And it's kind of your job to like get seen basically.

08:43.120 --> 08:44.560
And then you sort of start to poke around.

08:44.560 --> 08:45.520
Like, can I get you a coffee?

08:45.520 --> 08:46.320
Can I get you a tea?

08:47.760 --> 08:48.960
Can I go get your lunch?

08:48.960 --> 08:52.960
And that sort of, that's like, weirdly, like, I think

08:54.160 --> 08:56.880
I sort of just started just getting everyone's lunch for them.

08:56.880 --> 08:57.120
Yeah.

08:57.120 --> 08:58.320
And I remember this one incident.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.840
But you're an interest rate trader.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.600
Well, I mean, at first I was just an intern, right?

09:01.600 --> 09:02.480
So you're just an intern.

09:02.480 --> 09:03.680
So you've got no specific...

09:04.880 --> 09:05.680
You're just an intern.

09:05.680 --> 09:07.680
You need to get them to hire you to the desk basically.

09:07.680 --> 09:08.000
Right.

09:08.000 --> 09:09.760
And I remember I just used to try and get everybody lunch.

09:09.760 --> 09:12.800
I remember sort of one of my first, one of my first days,

09:12.800 --> 09:14.800
I got a load of people lunch and I took a little note

09:14.800 --> 09:16.720
of like how much everybody's lunch cost.

09:16.800 --> 09:21.200
And then I put the change on the table, exact, exact change

09:21.200 --> 09:22.880
next to the trader who paid for the lunches.

09:23.440 --> 09:25.360
And the trader just, he just looked at it.

09:25.360 --> 09:26.880
You know, like when somebody dropped some coins

09:26.880 --> 09:28.160
and people just looked, he looked at the money

09:28.160 --> 09:29.040
and he was like, what's that?

09:29.040 --> 09:30.320
And I was like, it's your change.

09:30.960 --> 09:33.440
And he was like, it just didn't say anything.

09:33.440 --> 09:36.160
And I was like, it's like Â£4.31.

09:36.160 --> 09:39.200
And he just slid it across the desk into his little drawer.

09:39.200 --> 09:41.120
And he looked at me right in the face and he said,

09:41.120 --> 09:42.720
on this desk, we keep the change.

09:42.720 --> 09:45.360
And I was thinking, these guys are fucking mad basically.

09:46.880 --> 09:48.240
But that's how it works basically.

09:48.240 --> 09:50.160
And then, you know, I started getting, you know,

09:50.560 --> 09:51.600
I got a lot of lunches.

09:52.720 --> 09:54.640
Eventually they sent me to get like lunch river on the floor.

09:54.640 --> 09:57.280
I think it was this kind of game dynamic

09:57.280 --> 09:59.520
because they knew that I wasn't from that space

09:59.520 --> 10:00.400
and they kind of loved it.

10:00.400 --> 10:01.760
And they were like, played little games with me.

10:01.760 --> 10:03.200
So like, on end of my internship,

10:03.200 --> 10:04.720
they sent me to buy burgers for everyone

10:04.720 --> 10:06.080
on the whole trading floor,

10:06.080 --> 10:07.920
which is like fucking 500 people or something.

10:07.920 --> 10:08.400
Right?

10:08.400 --> 10:09.360
Just called me over, Gary.

10:09.920 --> 10:11.360
Today I'm buying lunch river on the floor.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.360
And I knew they wanted me to be like,

10:13.360 --> 10:13.840
shitting myself.

10:13.840 --> 10:14.880
I was like, yeah, fine.

10:14.880 --> 10:15.680
So I did it.

10:15.680 --> 10:17.280
You know, I had to like get everyone involved.

10:17.280 --> 10:18.960
And then when I came back, I sat down

10:18.960 --> 10:20.400
after delivering burgers to everyone on the floor

10:20.400 --> 10:22.720
and they called me, Gary, Gary, you got a passport.

10:23.280 --> 10:25.680
And I was like, yeah, go home and get it.

10:25.680 --> 10:26.880
You're getting skiing.

10:26.880 --> 10:28.400
And that was like, honestly,

10:28.400 --> 10:29.920
the funniest thing about that was,

10:29.920 --> 10:31.440
I didn't even realize when you went skiing

10:31.440 --> 10:32.800
that you were in the mountains.

10:32.800 --> 10:33.840
You went to the top of the mountains.

10:34.560 --> 10:35.920
And it was like, fuck, you know, it was mad.

10:35.920 --> 10:38.480
I remember texting my dad, where's my passport on the train?

10:38.480 --> 10:39.760
So what did you think you were going like cross country

10:39.760 --> 10:40.800
skiing or something?

10:40.800 --> 10:43.040
I just, I only knew like Milton Key and Snowcenters

10:43.040 --> 10:43.920
is the only thing I could think of.

10:43.920 --> 10:45.680
I just thought it was like on a field or something.

10:45.680 --> 10:46.880
You know where I'm from.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.080
You don't, people don't go skiing.

10:48.080 --> 10:48.480
You know what I mean?

10:48.480 --> 10:49.280
I didn't know about that.

10:50.640 --> 10:51.840
But then that was how I got the job.

