01:08:47.520 --> 01:08:49.600
as an individual, as a family, as a community,

01:08:49.600 --> 01:08:52.640
because it genuinely is, I genuinely believe that.

01:08:52.640 --> 01:08:53.920
And if you don't do that,

01:08:53.920 --> 01:08:56.480
and you know, this thing recently where we suddenly saw,

01:08:57.200 --> 01:08:59.440
a lot of nice, well-off people messaging me,

01:08:59.440 --> 01:09:00.960
oh, my mortgage rate's going to go up,

01:09:00.960 --> 01:09:02.400
and then the government backs down,

01:09:02.400 --> 01:09:05.440
that is what happened when you act politically as a community.

01:09:05.440 --> 01:09:06.960
You force government to change.

01:09:07.600 --> 01:09:12.720
And I also understand that a lot of people are struggling financially,

01:09:12.720 --> 01:09:15.360
and they struggle to have the energy to act politically.

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:17.920
And you know, if you don't have anything to give,

01:09:17.920 --> 01:09:18.720
don't give anything.

01:09:18.720 --> 01:09:22.160
But if you have a little bit of space, a little bit of energy,

01:09:22.160 --> 01:09:23.600
you need to engage with this,

01:09:23.600 --> 01:09:25.200
because you are under attack,

01:09:25.200 --> 01:09:26.320
your houses are under attack,

01:09:26.320 --> 01:09:28.000
your living stands are under attack.

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:30.560
And the only way to push back is to be political.

01:09:30.560 --> 01:09:32.560
And you know, I come from a poor background,

01:09:32.560 --> 01:09:34.240
and people where I grew up don't want to be political.

01:09:34.240 --> 01:09:36.320
But the truth is, this is what happens if you're not political,

01:09:36.320 --> 01:09:37.280
you know, there's a fight going on.

01:09:37.280 --> 01:09:38.560
If you don't fight it, you lose.

01:09:41.360 --> 01:09:47.440
Yeah. Going back to that thing about renting and homeownership,

01:09:47.440 --> 01:09:49.200
because of course, if you say, well, we need,

01:09:49.200 --> 01:09:50.160
and I believe this,

01:09:50.160 --> 01:09:52.560
we need house prices to go down at least 10%, 15%,

01:09:52.560 --> 01:09:54.480
and then stagnate, basically, for 20 years.

01:09:55.680 --> 01:09:56.400
And then somebody would say,

01:09:56.400 --> 01:09:58.160
well, that means that somebody who's just bought a property here,

01:09:58.160 --> 01:10:02.000
and there might be a young viewer of yours living in, I don't know,

01:10:03.280 --> 01:10:04.400
Leicester, right?

01:10:04.400 --> 01:10:06.000
And they've just bought a nice terraced house,

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:08.720
nothing special, 230 grand,

01:10:08.720 --> 01:10:10.160
and they're going to go into negative equity.

01:10:10.720 --> 01:10:12.080
Okay, they go into negative equity,

01:10:12.080 --> 01:10:13.680
let's say for 18 months.

01:10:13.680 --> 01:10:15.280
I'd still rather be in their shoes,

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:17.360
paying towards an asset,

01:10:17.360 --> 01:10:19.120
which at least in the medium to long term,

01:10:19.120 --> 01:10:22.240
is going to be making cash than renting.

01:10:22.240 --> 01:10:24.960
I don't understand how people think the negative,

01:10:24.960 --> 01:10:26.480
you say negative equity and people go,

01:10:26.480 --> 01:10:27.680
oh my God, they start panicking.

01:10:28.240 --> 01:10:30.160
Renting is much worse than negative equity.

01:10:30.160 --> 01:10:31.920
I was renting in London for 15 years,

01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:33.920
I lost about 85 grand renting,

01:10:33.920 --> 01:10:35.040
I've got nothing to show for it.

01:10:35.680 --> 01:10:37.040
And yet in the popular imagination,

01:10:37.040 --> 01:10:39.840
somehow negative equity is way worse than renting.

01:10:39.840 --> 01:10:40.880
Yeah, I think what I say is,

01:10:40.880 --> 01:10:45.440
the problem actually is the house price to wage ratio.

01:10:45.440 --> 01:10:46.720
If you think about it, that's the problem.

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:50.480
That's gone up massively, 20 years ago, 30 years ago,

01:10:50.480 --> 01:10:51.840
that was like three or four,

01:10:51.840 --> 01:10:54.240
and now it's like in London, 20, 30 or more.

01:10:55.200 --> 01:10:56.960
So what you really want,

01:10:57.760 --> 01:10:59.360
you can fix the problem with that house price

01:10:59.360 --> 01:11:01.120
is coming down if you allow wages to rise.

01:11:01.120 --> 01:11:03.120
And I think what's interesting is in the last 20, 30 years,

01:11:03.120 --> 01:11:04.480
so we have the Bank of England,

01:11:04.480 --> 01:11:06.240
who have this mandate to keep inflation down.

01:11:07.120 --> 01:11:08.160
Except housing inflation.

01:11:08.800 --> 01:11:10.880
Exactly, it doesn't look at house prices.

01:11:10.880 --> 01:11:12.480
That inflation does not include house prices.

01:11:12.480 --> 01:11:15.200
So we have a mechanism that allows house prices to go up,

01:11:15.760 --> 01:11:17.600
but does not allow wages to go up.

01:11:17.600 --> 01:11:19.280
And because people want to avoid negative equity,

01:11:19.280 --> 01:11:20.640
we do not allow house prices to come down.

01:11:20.640 --> 01:11:22.480
So we've created an unfixable problem.

01:11:22.480 --> 01:11:24.160
If you allow house prices to go up,

01:11:24.160 --> 01:11:25.760
and you simultaneously will not accept

01:11:25.760 --> 01:11:28.240
falling house prices or rising wages,

01:11:28.240 --> 01:11:29.760
then that problem is unfixable.

01:11:29.760 --> 01:11:31.040
And I think we need to accept

01:11:31.040 --> 01:11:32.480
that we have a problem here,

01:11:32.480 --> 01:11:35.120
and we need to look realistically,

01:11:35.120 --> 01:11:37.280
why is this so big, and how do we bring wages up?

01:11:37.280 --> 01:11:39.520
In my opinion, the reason that

01:11:39.520 --> 01:11:41.200
this market has become so big

01:11:41.200 --> 01:11:43.440
is because the rich are so fucking rich now,

01:11:43.440 --> 01:11:44.880
and these guys buy assets.

01:11:44.880 --> 01:11:46.640
It's not just houses that have gone up,

01:11:46.640 --> 01:11:48.560
land prices gone up, stocks have gone up,

01:11:48.560 --> 01:11:49.840
luxury cars have gone up,

01:11:49.840 --> 01:11:52.000
luxury art has gone up, gold has gone up.

01:11:52.080 --> 01:11:54.800
Every single asset has rocketed in price

01:11:54.800 --> 01:11:56.640
because the rich are unbelievably rich.

01:11:56.640 --> 01:11:57.680
People need to understand,

01:11:59.200 --> 01:12:00.640
ultimately, there is a competition here

01:12:00.640 --> 01:12:01.440
for who owns the assets.

01:12:02.080 --> 01:12:04.800
And if you allow the rich to be unbelievably rich,

01:12:04.800 --> 01:12:05.920
think about it like this, right?

01:12:05.920 --> 01:12:08.640
Imagine you are, Elon Musk is a billion or whatever,

01:12:08.640 --> 01:12:09.920
but imagine you've got 100 million quid.

01:12:09.920 --> 01:12:12.480
Imagine that's your net worth, 100 million quid.

01:12:12.480 --> 01:12:13.920
You will make on that wealth

01:12:13.920 --> 01:12:15.200
about five million pounds a year.

01:12:15.920 --> 01:12:16.560
Let's say four.

01:12:17.120 --> 01:12:18.240
You make four million pounds a year

01:12:18.240 --> 01:12:19.120
just for getting out of bed.

01:12:19.120 --> 01:12:19.920
How much do you spend?

01:12:20.880 --> 01:12:21.760
Per day.

01:12:22.320 --> 01:12:22.800
Per year.

01:12:23.600 --> 01:12:25.600
I could live on 15 grand a year easily.

01:12:25.600 --> 01:12:27.200
Well, you're making four million pounds a year.

01:12:27.200 --> 01:12:28.400
Yeah, but honestly, I mean,

01:12:28.400 --> 01:12:30.160
as me, being a slightly 30 grand a year,

01:12:30.160 --> 01:12:31.520
40 grand a year easily.

01:12:31.520 --> 01:12:35.200
A sensible person would spend 200, 300 grand a year,

01:12:35.200 --> 01:12:36.560
live a life of luxury,

01:12:36.560 --> 01:12:38.720
and use the other 3.7 million pounds

01:12:38.720 --> 01:12:40.480
to buy more assets.

01:12:40.480 --> 01:12:41.120
That's what they do.

01:12:41.120 --> 01:12:42.960
And it's not that they're evil.

01:12:42.960 --> 01:12:43.840
I don't hate these people.

01:12:43.840 --> 01:12:44.720
They're not bad people.

01:12:44.720 --> 01:12:46.400
It's just, if you're super rich,

01:12:46.400 --> 01:12:47.920
you have a massive income.

01:12:47.920 --> 01:12:49.440
And it happens automatically.

01:12:49.440 --> 01:12:50.320
You just put it in the stock market.

01:12:50.320 --> 01:12:51.360
Those are the incentives.

01:12:51.360 --> 01:12:52.960
Yeah, you know, and that's so...

01:12:52.960 --> 01:12:54.720
You create this vacuum of wealth

01:12:54.720 --> 01:12:56.480
that sucks wealth out of ordinary family.

01:12:56.480 --> 01:12:57.920
So, of course, how's prices going to rise?

01:12:57.920 --> 01:12:59.280
Because they have got so much money,

01:12:59.280 --> 01:13:00.160
they're going to push it up.

01:13:00.160 --> 01:13:00.960
Let me ask you a question

01:13:00.960 --> 01:13:01.840
that I'm actually relating to this,

01:13:01.840 --> 01:13:03.600
because at Labour Party Conference,

01:13:03.600 --> 01:13:04.880
Keir Starmer outlined a policy,

01:13:05.440 --> 01:13:06.640
and he said he wanted home ownership

01:13:06.640 --> 01:13:08.480
to go from 65% to 70%.

01:13:08.480 --> 01:13:10.080
It was 70% in 2003.

01:13:10.080 --> 01:13:12.320
So, important to say, we've gone backwards, right?

01:13:13.120 --> 01:13:14.080
And that they would do this

01:13:14.080 --> 01:13:17.360
basically through some government-led mortgage scheme,

01:13:17.360 --> 01:13:19.440
presumably they would provide deposits to people.

01:13:19.440 --> 01:13:20.480
I don't know how they would do it.

01:13:21.280 --> 01:13:22.400
They could be subprime mortgages,

01:13:22.400 --> 01:13:23.760
presumably, which are backed by the state.

01:13:23.760 --> 01:13:24.400
I have no idea.

01:13:25.680 --> 01:13:26.960
That to me sounds like

01:13:26.960 --> 01:13:28.160
you're only going to further inflate

01:13:28.160 --> 01:13:29.040
the mortgage market, though,

01:13:29.040 --> 01:13:32.400
because, of course, going from 65% to 70% again

01:13:32.400 --> 01:13:34.800
means you've got massive increase in demand.

01:13:34.800 --> 01:13:36.640
Good, I'm happy to do that.

01:13:36.640 --> 01:13:38.240
But that doesn't sound like a solution to me,

01:13:38.240 --> 01:13:40.240
if you're saying we're going to help home ownership

01:13:40.240 --> 01:13:42.080
by increasing prices,

01:13:42.080 --> 01:13:44.400
and, again, they're going to out ship wage increases.

01:13:44.400 --> 01:13:46.880
I think this is what happens when you don't deal

01:13:46.880 --> 01:13:47.920
with the fundamental problem

01:13:47.920 --> 01:13:50.000
that inequality is increasing massively.

01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:51.760
You know, how do you keep people in homes

01:13:51.760 --> 01:13:53.360
when inequality is increasing massively?

01:13:53.360 --> 01:13:56.880
You know, if you have this constant flow of wealth and assets

01:13:56.880 --> 01:13:59.520
from ordinary families to the rich,

01:13:59.520 --> 01:14:00.720
then how do you keep them in their homes?

01:14:00.720 --> 01:14:01.920
The only way to do it,

01:14:01.920 --> 01:14:03.360
because homes are ultimately

01:14:03.360 --> 01:14:05.760
the largest form of wealth in the country,

01:14:05.760 --> 01:14:08.320
the only way to do it is have massive increase in debt.

01:14:08.320 --> 01:14:09.600
And this is, if you start looking

01:14:09.600 --> 01:14:10.960
for sort of technocratic solutions,

01:14:11.520 --> 01:14:12.080
this is what will happen.

01:14:12.080 --> 01:14:14.080
You'll just end up putting people into more and more debt.

01:14:14.080 --> 01:14:15.520
And I think that is what will happen.

01:14:15.520 --> 01:14:20.080
And we need, people need to understand

01:14:20.080 --> 01:14:22.160
that you cannot be rich without assets.

01:14:22.160 --> 01:14:25.280
And the current setup sees an enormous flow of assets

01:14:25.280 --> 01:14:26.800
and wealth and money every year

01:14:26.800 --> 01:14:28.400
from ordinary families to the rich.

01:14:28.400 --> 01:14:30.240
You know, you make 30 grand,

01:14:30.240 --> 01:14:34.000
you spend all of that on mortgage, rent, food, bills, energy.

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:35.120
That money doesn't disappear.

01:14:35.120 --> 01:14:36.480
It goes to the owner of your house,

01:14:36.480 --> 01:14:37.520
the owner of your mortgage,

01:14:37.520 --> 01:14:39.200
the owner of the food, the owner of Tesco,

01:14:39.200 --> 01:14:40.720
the owner of the energy companies, right?

01:14:41.280 --> 01:14:44.080
You earn 30 grand, you give all of it to the rich.

01:14:44.080 --> 01:14:46.000
And it is that guy, Rishi Sunaki,

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:47.520
he's worth 700 million pounds, right?

01:14:47.520 --> 01:14:49.520
You know, he will make every year,

01:14:50.400 --> 01:14:52.640
he'll make 20 million pounds on that every single year.

01:14:52.640 --> 01:14:54.800
And that's where your mortgage payment goes.

01:14:54.800 --> 01:14:56.960
You know, so if you create a system

01:14:56.960 --> 01:14:58.880
where there's this enormous flow of money,

01:14:58.880 --> 01:15:01.840
wealth assets from ordinary families to the rich,

01:15:01.840 --> 01:15:04.000
then year after year, generation after generation,

01:15:04.000 --> 01:15:06.560
ordinary families will get poorer.

01:15:07.200 --> 01:15:09.520
And this fundamentally needs to be fixed on it

01:15:09.520 --> 01:15:10.880
until we grasp this problem,

01:15:11.440 --> 01:15:12.560
life will get worse and worse.

01:15:12.560 --> 01:15:14.400
That is exactly why I do the job that I do.

01:15:14.400 --> 01:15:15.280
I don't need to do this.

01:15:15.280 --> 01:15:16.080
You know what I mean?

01:15:16.080 --> 01:15:17.120
I've made a lot of money

01:15:17.120 --> 01:15:18.160
and I could keep making more money.

01:15:18.160 --> 01:15:20.000
I could go live on a beach in the Philippines,

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:23.760
but poverty will explode if we don't deal with this.

01:15:23.760 --> 01:15:25.040
Let's talk about deficits.

01:15:25.040 --> 01:15:26.480
It's a word that's not mentioned anymore.

01:15:26.480 --> 01:15:29.440
