Actually, it's important to say,

01:15:38.960 --> 01:15:40.960
we've been running virtually permanent deficits

01:15:40.960 --> 01:15:42.320
since the late 1970s.

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:45.520
For the Tories, quote unquote,

01:15:45.520 --> 01:15:48.400
balancing the books is always this big watchword.

01:15:48.960 --> 01:15:50.880
Are they ever going to balance the books?

01:15:50.880 --> 01:15:51.520
Which is to say,

01:15:51.520 --> 01:15:53.600
are they ever going to preside over a situation

01:15:53.600 --> 01:15:56.720
where actually they bring in more through general taxation

01:15:56.720 --> 01:15:58.560
than they spend through public spending?

01:15:58.560 --> 01:16:00.000
Because they promised to do that for years.

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:00.880
It never happens.

01:16:00.880 --> 01:16:02.640
I think it will probably never happen.

01:16:03.200 --> 01:16:04.160
Okay, so, you know,

01:16:04.160 --> 01:16:05.760
lots of people have lots of strong opinions on this.

01:16:06.560 --> 01:16:08.320
Governments don't need to run surpluses.

01:16:08.320 --> 01:16:09.200
You can run a deficit.

01:16:09.200 --> 01:16:11.840
The reason is because deficits get eroded over time

01:16:11.840 --> 01:16:14.320
by both economic growth and by inflation.

01:16:15.040 --> 01:16:17.600
So, your debt is fixed in nominal terms.

01:16:17.600 --> 01:16:18.800
Inflation pushed all the prices up.

01:16:18.800 --> 01:16:20.240
So, if you have growth of,

01:16:20.240 --> 01:16:21.200
nowadays we don't get much,

01:16:21.200 --> 01:16:22.480
but if you get one, two percent,

01:16:22.480 --> 01:16:24.080
if you have inflation of two, three percent,

01:16:24.080 --> 01:16:25.760
then your deficit is naturally falling

01:16:25.760 --> 01:16:28.960
relative to the size of your economy by four or five percent every year.

01:16:28.960 --> 01:16:32.720
So, you can afford to run a four or five percent deficit over time.

01:16:32.720 --> 01:16:33.680
You can, if that's what you want.

01:16:34.560 --> 01:16:35.840
I'm not opposed to deficits at all.

01:16:35.920 --> 01:16:40.560
I think the last few years,

01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:42.400
I've seen some people sort of pushing this direction

01:16:42.400 --> 01:16:43.920
of let's run massive deficits.

01:16:43.920 --> 01:16:48.160
And I think the deficit in Corridor is necessary.

01:16:48.160 --> 01:16:52.400
I think the big problem that this sort of people saying

01:16:52.400 --> 01:16:53.760
let's run massive deficits is,

01:16:54.320 --> 01:16:57.040
it totally defangs people like me saying,

01:16:57.040 --> 01:16:58.400
